ventilate /ˈvɛntɪˌleɪt/

(ventilating,ventilated,ventilates) 

1. V-T If you ventilate a room or building, you allow fresh air to get into it. 使通风 

例： Ventilate the room properly when stripping paint. 在刮漆的时候要适当地使房间通风。 

2. ventilation N-UNCOUNT 通风 

例： The only ventilation comes from tiny sliding windows. 惟一的通风来自几扇小小的推拉窗。

